issue.title: Workouts don't follow the curve

milestone.title: Push to Publish: 1.0.0
milestone.description: Fixing up all of the bugs in the app, adding P0 functionality, so that the app is ready to be put on the app store.

issue.body:
Sometimes the workouts chosen don't follow the curves they should. In the case of increasing, it jumps from 96bpm, 110bpm, _94bpm_, 127bpm.  I think the issue is because the song list generator blindly looks for songs that are closest to the target bpm, but not already in the current list, so we've already stepped through everything nearby, then the 'closest' song is actually super far away. 

There's not really a clearly solution for this. Do we repeat a song?  Always find a song in the direction of the curve, even if it's clearly too far? Any chance we can slow down/speed up songs dynamically a smidge?

issue.title: Reject outling taps in the tap-input to get a better measurements

milestone.title: Push to Publish: 1.0.0
milestone.description: Fixing up all of the bugs in the app, adding P0 functionality, so that the app is ready to be put on the app store.

issue.body:
My thoughts right now are to dynamically analyze the taps so far, and after 5 or so, start discarding taps where the difference between them and previous taps are outliers, and then collect until there are enough samples to make a conclusive decision on the bpm (maybe when variance hits a low point after discarding outliers). 

Seems pretty easy to do, but we'd have to refactor the code in BPMFinderMusicActivity into a little counter object, which I'll probably do. Won't be able to start on it until this weekend though.

issue.body: Don't have the specific info on me, but I started the app on an emulator running Marshmellow, and it crashed on startup. The issue ended up being something relation to Runtime permissions: some resources on it are [here](http://developer.android.com/about/versions/marshmallow/android-6.0-changes.html#behavior-runtime-permissions). Should fix soon.

issue.title: Rotation restarts the tapping process

milestone.title: Push to Publish: 1.0.0
milestone.description: Fixing up all of the bugs in the app, adding P0 functionality, so that the app is ready to be put on the app store.

issue.body: From Jemitk: "Every time the screen rotation is detected, it will start the onStart() method in that activity. Currently, the "let's start tapping!" screen will restart everytime I rotate the screen on the "tap the heart to the beat" one and restart the entire song library again. Has to be fixed!"
